t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-field-group elementor-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-601afa4 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"601afa4\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ebb9561\" data-id=\"ebb9561\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d39f88b elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"d39f88b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Importance of identifying carpenter ants as a pest<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-eb8ac9a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"eb8ac9a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Carpenter ants are a common pest that can cause significant damage to homes and other structures. These ants are attracted to moist or decaying wood, which they use as a nesting site. Once inside the structure, carpenter ants can chew through walls, floors, and ceilings, causing structural damage over time. Identifying carpenter ants as a pest is crucial because prompt action is necessary to prevent further building destruction.<\/p><p>It&#8217;s essential to know how to identify carpenter ants correctly. These insects have distinctive physical characteristics that set them apart from other ant species. Carpenter ants are typically larger than most other ant species and have dark-colored bodies with segmented waists and large mandibles. They&#8217;re also usually black or dark brown in color.<\/p><p>Ignoring the presence of carpenter ants can lead to severe consequences for homeowners. The longer these pests remain undetected, the more significant the damage they can cause becomes. It&#8217;s vital to take immediate action upon identifying carpenter ants infestation by contacting professional pest control services, which will develop an effective plan for eliminating these pests from your home while preventing future infestations from occurring again.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cb42e7e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"cb42e7e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Characteristics and Behavior of Carpenter Ants<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-428056c elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"428056c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Carpenter ants are known for their large size and wood-destroying behavior. They can grow up to 1 inch in length and have a black or reddish-brown coloration. Unlike termites, carpenter ants do not eat wood but instead excavate it to create their nests, which can cause significant damage to wooden structures if left uncontrolled.<\/p><p>Carpenter ant\u2019s colonies consist of different castes that perform specific tasks such as reproduction, foraging, and nest maintenance. The queen is responsible for laying eggs while the workers gather food and maintain the nest. These ants prefer moist environments and often build their nests in decaying wood or areas with water damage.<\/p><p>When disturbed or threatened, carpenter ants may bite using their strong mandibles as a defense mechanism. They are also known for being active at night and can be attracted to sweet foods such as honey or sugar. Proper identification and elimination of carpenter ant colonies are important to prevent further structural damage to your property.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-79e799e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"79e799e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Signs of a carpenter ant infestation<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b890870 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b890870\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Carpenter ants are capable of causing significant property damage, and it is important to identify their presence as soon as possible. One of the most common signs of a carpenter&#8217;s ant infestation is the appearance of sawdust or wood shavings near baseboards, window sills, and other wooden structures. The ants create this debris as they tunnel through walls and other wooden surfaces for food.<\/p><p>Another sign to look out for is the presence of winged ants, especially during the spring and summer months. These winged ants are reproductive males and females who have left their original colony to search for new nesting sites. It may indicate an established carpenter ant colony nearby if you spot these winged ants inside your home or near its exterior walls.<\/p><p>Other potential indicators include:<\/p><ul><li>Rustling sounds from within walls or ceilings.<\/li><li>Holes in wooden surfaces with visible trails leading into them.<\/li><li>Sightings of live ants crawling around on floors or counters.<\/li><\/ul><p>If you suspect a carpenter ant infestation in your home, it is crucial to contact a pest control professional immediately before any further damage can occur.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-fd199cd elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"fd199cd\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-3211229\" data-id=\"3211229\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-inner-section elementor-element elementor-element-43e1ad6 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"43e1ad6\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-e9a5482\" data-id=\"e9a5482\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1e22936 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"1e22936\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Structural damage caused by carpenter ants<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8c8f1af elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"8c8f1af\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Carpenter ants are a common pest in Canada that can cause significant damage to homes and other buildings. These ants are well known for their ability to damage wooden structures as they excavate wood to create their nests. While some homeowners may assume that carpenter ants are not as destructive as termites, this misconception can lead to delayed extermination and further damage to the structure. Although the damage caused by carpenter ants may not be as serious as that caused by termites, large carpenter ant colonies are still capable of causing structural damage over time. The risks to homes and other buildings from carpenter ants are significant. These ants can weaken the structural integrity of wooden components such as beams, joists, and studs, leading to structural failure and costly repairs. In addition, carpenter ants can cause cosmetic damage to wooden surfaces, reducing the aesthetic appeal and value of a home or building.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-8c61ef1\" data-id=\"8c61ef1\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7f6bdef elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"7f6bdef\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/elementor\/thumbs\/carpenter-ants-damages-q3q9450k4ojtaq7aquo9wco6wwe0lw8aah8qzj7i3s.jpg\" title=\"carpenter ants damages\" alt=\"carpenter ants damages\" loading=\"lazy\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-4384939 elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"4384939\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-55117ea\" data-id=\"55117ea\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-c66d79a\" data-id=\"c66d79a\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bfd95a5 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"bfd95a5\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Residential Pest Control Service<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7a893c0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"7a893c0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Customized pest control treatments can be used to safeguard your living space against bothersome pests and ensure that they don&#8217;t become a nuisance in your home.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-aebb6ed elementor-align-center elementor-widget elementor-widget-global elementor-global-4670 elementor-widget-button\" data-id=\"aebb6ed\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"button.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-button-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t<a class=\"elementor-button elementor-button-link elementor-size-lg\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/appointment\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Book An Appointment<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-b1b864c\" data-id=\"b1b864c\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-93b58d0 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"93b58d0\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-8aa1897\" data-id=\"8aa1897\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6ec7b2e elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"6ec7b2e\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Prevention and Control of Carpenter Ants<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d0cba66 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d0cba66\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Carpenter Ants are common pests in homes and businesses, and their colonies can quickly become a nuisance. Here are a few tips to help you prevent and control Carpenter Ants:<\/p><p><strong>Keep your home clean and organized:<\/strong>\u00a0Ants are attracted to dirty and cluttered surroundings, so keep them clean and organized to reduce their chances of nesting.<\/p><p><strong>Seal cracks and openings:<\/strong>\u00a0Ants use cracks and openings in surfaces as pathways and food sources, so seal these areas to prevent them from entering your home.<\/p><p><strong>Use baits and traps:<\/strong> Ant baits and traps are a great way to trap and kill Carpenter Ants. Baits can be placed around the perimeter of your home, and traps can be set in areas where the ants are active.<\/p><p><strong>Contact ACME Pest Solutions:<\/strong>\u00a0If you notice Carpenter Ants in your home or business, contact ACME Pest Solutions for help. Our team is dedicated to helping homeowners and businesses prevent and control these pests.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Carpenter Ants Identification Color size Description Color Carpenter Ants typically have a black or reddish-brown body, with some species displaying a combination of both colors. size Carpenter ants are known for their large size, reaching up to 13 millimeters in length. Description Carpenter ant&#8217;s bodies are divided into three segments: the head, thorax, and abdomen. &#8230; <a title=\"Carpenter Ants\" class=\"read-more\" href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/carpenter-ants\/\" aria-label=\"More on Carpenter Ants\">Read more<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"rank_math_lock_modified_date":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[37],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-6037","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-pest-libraries"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6037"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=6037"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/6037\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=6037"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=6037"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=6037"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}